The paper deals with empirical risk minimization, which is a fundamental concept in machine learning and falls under the category of statistical learning theory. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of hypothesis classes and Rademacher complexity suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on smooth loss functions and non-negative objectives could also place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
